The paper discusses off-policy reinforcement learning using a fixed offline dataset, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on deep RL algorithms and their performance on the DQN replay dataset, which is related to computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper uses the Atari 2600 games as a benchmark, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
